  "text": "The LLVM SelectionDAG assertion 'Cannot expand this type; LLVM lacks the right hooks' traces to the type legalization infrastructure in llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/.\n\n1. **Error location**: The expansion failure is reported in `llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/LegalizeIntegerTypes.cpp`. The function `DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntegerResult` (starting at line 3024) contains a switch statement with a default case (lines 3034-3040) that calls `report_fatal_error(\"Do not know how to expand the result of this operator!\")` when no expansion handler is found for a given integer type operation. Similarly, `LegalizeFloatTypes.cpp` has an analogous pattern in `ExpandFloatResult`.\n\n2. **Orchestrating function**: `DAGTypeLegalizer::run()` in `llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/LegalizeTypes.cpp` drives the entire type legalization process, dispatching to type-specific handlers (ExpandIntegerResult, ExpandFloatResult, etc.) based on the type action.\n\n3. **EVT class**: The `EVT` (Extended Value Type) struct is defined in `llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/ValueTypes.h` (line 35). Its `isSimple()` method (lines 137-139) tests whether a type is a simple MVT vs. an extended type, returning true if `V.SimpleTy != MVT::INVALID_SIMPLE_VALUE_TYPE`.\n\n4. **LegalizeDAG class**: The `SelectionDAGLegalize` class is defined in `llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/LegalizeDAG.cpp` (line 88). It orchestrates operation-level legalization after type legalization completes. The `DAGTypeLegalizer` class itself is declared in `llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/LegalizeTypes.h`.\n\n5. **Type conversion**: `TargetLoweringBase::getTypeConversion()` in `llvm/lib/CodeGen/TargetLoweringBase.cpp` (line 1329) determines what legalization action to take for any given type, returning LegalizeKind enums that guide the expansion process."
}

